title: opt-level = 'z': The compilation is successful and an error is reported when running

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
### Code ```Rust System: windows 10 RUST_BACKTRACE=full [profile.release] lto = true opt-level = 'z' cargo build --release 1. The compilation is correct without any errors and warnings; 2. runtime is error out println: Backtrace 3. The program is still running and does not crash 4. The logstore is no longer working: crate: log 5. If I set opt-level = 's' , No error will be reported ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` cargo 1.57.0 (b2e52d7ca 2021-10-21) ``` ### Cargo.lock ``` [Cargo.lock.txt](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/files/7690706/Cargo.lock.txt) [Cargo.toml.txt](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/files/7691281/Cargo.toml.txt) ```
